          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2327-Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2327-Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2327-Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong>,<strong> red onion wedges</strong> and <strong>cherry tomatoes </strong>to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Add your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until the vegetables are soft and the potatoes are crisp – this is your <strong>caprese bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2327-Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
